reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Simple, elegant, light, sturdy lamp with adjustable light modes, brightness, and angles
reviews.reviewText: I love this simple, elegant lamp, and I have found myself moving it all around the house, especially during these short, dark days! Once put together, the lamp feels graceful and solid, and looks nice anywhere I have put it.For some time, I have wanted a low-profile floor lamp that is easy to relocate and allows easy and free adjustment of the angle and intensity of the light, as well as offering the option to switch to different color temperatures. This is exactly what I have found in this lamp.I am very happy with the operations and quality of the light produced as well as the different color temperatures and light levels. The rocker switch operation is simple: One switch for the 2 light modes and one switch for the 2 brightness options plus off.The slender light head is almost 12-inches long and produces an even, un-flickering and pleasant light. I really like the long LED light. The adjustable arm is also about 12-inches long and allows unlimited directional adjustment. I am loving that I can point the light in any direction at any angle.I have found the lamp to be stable when using it, even while bending the adjustable arm around and around to find where I want it. While the lamp is light and compact, the tripod feet keep it from rocking or tipping.The assembly was very fast and simple. There are three height configurations it could be assembled to: 2-foot, 3-1/2 foot and about 5-1/2 foot configurations. This is a great feature! I assembled it to 5-1/2 feet. In this configuration, from the floor to the tip of the light is about 6-feet in a straight line.The plug is, of course, a standard USB-A plug and requires a USB outlet or adaptor (not included), which I have in abundance. The cable is about 5-1/2 feet long, with the switch control sitting about 8-inches from where the cable connects to the lamp. This puts the switch about 27-inches from the floor with the 5-1/2 foot configuration. For me this puts the switch exactly at the perfect height for using it from the bed, where I use it for reading.I am very happy with the lamp and would not hesitate to purchase another for myself or for someone else.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 1, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Awesome Simple, Minimalist LED Floor Lamp
reviews.reviewText: I have been using this floor lamp in my craft room for the past week and I love it. It is sleek and modern looking (not big and bulky). Having the different temperature levels as well as light levels is a plus. It can be softer glow lighting shining off the wall with the bendable neck when I am organizing my materials or watching a crafting how to video, and it can be brighter cool lighting when working on craft tasks that need focused lighting.It arrived packaged well (so small and thus easy to pack/move) and was quick to set up. It is lightweight and easy to move, but also sturdy and stable when in place.The plug is a standard USB and does require a USB outlet or adaptor (which is not included). My craft room has an outlet with built in USB, so I was able to plug in the lamp and use immediately.Overall I am very happy with this reasonably priced (especially with coupon) LED lamp and would recommend it as a great option to add lighting to any room.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 26, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A perfect little light for lots of reasons
reviews.reviewText: This little light is just wonderful. It has exceeded my expectations! First of all, it assembles easily and is really more stout than I thought it would be. It's got a perfect base (three legs) and is a perfect height. It doesn't wiggle or wobble. The top 18" or so of the upright is flexible - so can be used to point the light in any direction. There are two switches - one determines the type of light - daylight (natural) or brighter white. The second switch determines the brightness. I use the brighter white color along with the higher (brighter) setting. As I write this - it is pointed at my desk and keyboard. I have no other lights on in my office and it is perfect. No glare, it's not in my way, and it's the perfect brightness - I can see everything on my desk without flooding my office with too much additional light. Be advised that it plugs into a USB outlet - not a regular wall outlet - unless you want to use an adaptor (which is not included). I love it and I would buy it again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good for Beginners and Travelling
reviews.reviewText: This lamp is great for beginner lash techs or beauticians, its easy to assemble and pretty portable. It does have a lot of parts, since the bottom tripod part has to be assembled, but that part is small enough that you can keep it assembled and store it wherever. The brightness is pretty good for the price, it's got a cool and warm setting, and a low and high setting for each. The high isn't always bright enough, but it gets the job done. I gave it 4 stars because the plug in is annoying, it's a USB type instead of a prong plug so you have to carry a USB-prong block with you if you travel. I also think it's good material since it's made out of metal, but it could be sturdier. I like the fact that the lighting part is attached to the metal part with a flexible material, which makes travel and storing easy, plug it's nice to move around wherever you need, but that makes it kinda wobbly. Like I said in the beginning of this review, it's great for beginners or those looking for a cheaper option.
